title: HTC Touch Diamond - TomTom 7 inc Scandinavian Maps
description:
Follow the directions and all will work perfect!

* Copy TomTom_Navigator_7.450.9028.cab to your HTC Touch

* Run the file from your phone.

* In your TomTom map on phone you find "ttnavigator.bif". Open the file and remember the "DeviceUniqueID". You will need it later.

* Copy the folder "Scandinavia" to your "My Documents" folder on your phone.

* NOW copy the "Scandinavia-14.meta" from your map folder. And copy it to the "patch/insert_meta_from_Map_here/" folder.

* Run "RunMe English" application and enter the DeviceUniceID when asked to.

* Now a file named "Scandinavia-14.meta.dct" is in your "insert_meta_from_Map_here" folder. Copy this file to you TomTom map folder.


Start Tom Tom and the map should work. I did it this way and it worked. I can garantee (On My HTC Touch Diamond)! 
But I was trying for some hours before I fixed it. 
Hopefully you will fix it fast now :)


When everything work you can copy the "voices" folder to your TomTom root folder. For enable the speaking feature.

Good Luck and happy traveling
MustangMannen
